    <item>
      <title>Docs: Storage</title>
      <link>https://deps.cloud/docs/deploy/config/storage/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://deps.cloud/docs/deploy/config/storage/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;deps.cloud was built with portability in mind.
As a result, we wanted to support common relational database systems that we could expect at other companies.
While not officially supported, you could replace the specific technology with a protocol compatible equivalent.
For example, you might replace &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mysql.com/&#34;&gt;MySQL&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=&#34;https://mariadb.org/&#34;&gt;MariaDB&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&#34;https://vitess.io/&#34;&gt;Vitess&lt;/a&gt;.
Or &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.postgresql.org/&#34;&gt;PostgreSQL&lt;/a&gt; with something like &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cockroachlabs.com/&#34;&gt;CockroachDB&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
